Package: skedastic
Type: Package
Title: Heteroskedasticity Diagnostics for Linear Regression Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Thomas", "Farrar", email = "tjfarrar@alumni.uwaterloo.ca", 
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package contains functions implementing numerous methods for 
    detecting heteroskedasticity (sometimes called 
    heteroscedasticity) in the classical linear regression model. 
    Homoskedasticity refers to the assumption of constant variance that is 
    imposed on the model errors (disturbances); heteroskedasticity is the 
    violation of this assumption.
RdMacros: Rdpack
